<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/FRIPIN-2">
<title>Friedland, Julian: Philosophy Is Not a Science</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/FRIPIN-2</link>
<description>_The New York Times_ 1. 2012The intellectual culture of scientism clouds our understanding of science itself. What&#x2019;s more, it eclipses alternative ways of knowing &#x2014; chiefly the philosophical &#x2014; that can actually yield greater certainty than the scientific. While science and philosophy do at times overlap, they are fundamentally different approaches to understanding. So philosophers should not add to the conceptual confusion that subsumes all knowledge into science. Rather, we should underscore the fact that various disciplines we ordinarily treat as science are at least as &#x2014; if not more &#x2014;philosophical than scientific.&#x3C;div&#x3E;(&#x3C;a href=&#x22;https://philpapers.org/go.pl?id=FRIPIN-2&#x26;amp;proxyId=&#x26;amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fopinionator.blogs.nytimes.com%2F2012%2F04%2F05%2Fphilosophy-is-not-a-science%2F&#x22;&#x3E;direct link&#x3C;/a&#x3E;)&#x3C;/div&#x3E;</description>
