</item>
<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/STIRTC-4">
<title>Stichter, Matt: Replies to Commentators on The Skillfulness of Virtue</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/STIRTC-4</link>
<description>_Ethical Theory and Moral Practice_ 24 (2):611-623. 2021First, let me start by thanking all of my commentators for doing a careful reading of my book, providing me with lots of though-provoking responses, and on top of all of that for the significant time commitment in being a part of this symposium. I&#x2019;m very grateful for all the support! Let me add a further note of thanks to Noell Birondo for taking on the role of editor in bringing all of these wonderful contributions together in this issue of Ethical Theory and Moral Practice.&#x3C;div&#x3E;(&#x3C;a href=&#x22;https://philpapers.org/go.pl?id=STIRTC-4&#x26;amp;proxyId=&#x26;amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2F10.1007%2Fs10677-021-10197-1&#x22;&#x3E;direct link&#x3C;/a&#x3E;)&#x3C;/div&#x3E;</description>
