<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/TSAAWA">
<title>Tsai, Cheng-Hung: Artificial wisdom: a philosophical framework</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/TSAAWA</link>
<description>_AI and Society_:937-944. 2020Human excellences such as intelligence, morality, and consciousness are investigated by philosophers as well as artificial intelligence researchers. One excellence that has not been widely discussed by AI researchers is practical wisdom, the highest human excellence, or the highest, seventh, stage in Dreyfus&#x2019;s model of skill acquisition. In this paper, I explain why artificial wisdom matters and how artificial wisdom is possible (in principle and in practice) by responding to two philosophical challenges to building artificial wisdom systems. The result is a conceptual framework that guides future research on creating artificial wisdom.&#x3C;div&#x3E;(&#x3C;a href=&#x22;https://philpapers.org/go.pl?id=TSAAWA&#x26;amp;proxyId=&#x26;amp;u=http%3A%2F%2Frdcu.be%2Fb14tm&#x22;&#x3E;direct link&#x3C;/a&#x3E;)&#x3C;/div&#x3E;</description>
