<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/AMOAGA">
<title>Amoli, Ayatollah Javadi: A Glance At Sadr- Ul- Mutaallehin&#x27;s Transcendent Wisdom</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/AMOAGA</link>
<description>To shed light on Transcendent Wisdom in comparison with other schools, the author has in seven detailed chapters elaborated on issues such as manifestation of justice in Transcendent Wisdom, Mulla Sadra&#x27;s interpretation of the intelligible life&#x22; and his intellectual development.Ayatollah Javadi Amoli considers demonstration, gnosis and the Quran as the founding elements of Transcendent Wisdom. To reach this wisdom,the soul must set off the four journeys through trans - substantial motion.The author emphasizes that Transcendent Wisdom is more comprehensive than speculative mysticism, illuminationist theosophy and Peripateticism thanks to its incomparably inclusive nature.</description>
