<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/THOPWA-2">
<title>Thomason, Neil Ryland: Philosophical Wisdom and Linguistic Knowledge: The Value and Future of Analytic Philosophy</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/THOPWA-2</link>
<description>Can conceptual analysis give more than semantic information? ;It can if there is independent reason to believe that the words of the language mark distinctions of particular value. Austin&#x27;s argument for this being generally the case fails, but with a reformulation of what an analysis should be like, one can test a concept&#x27;s usefulness. ;This, in turn, leads to a different account of the origin of philosophical paradoxes</description>
