<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/RTLO-4">
<title>R., T. L.: The Lure of Wisdom</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/RTLO-4</link>
<description>_Review of Metaphysics_ 16 (3):580-580. 1963In this Aquinas lecture the author defends the idea of wisdom as a valid and valuable topic for philosophic discussion. Collins devotes most of his energies to explaining the largely neglected Cartesian view of wisdom. He concludes that by the method of &#x22;metaphysical ingression&#x22; we can give the subject of wisdom its proper close connection with the whole of metaphysics.--R. T. L.&#x3C;div&#x3E;(&#x3C;a href=&#x22;https://philpapers.org/go.pl?id=RTLO-4&#x26;amp;proxyId=&#x26;amp;u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pdcnet.org%2Fcollection%2Fshow%3Fid%3Drevmetaph_1963_0016_0003_0580_0580d%26file_type%3Dpdf&#x22;&#x3E;direct link&#x3C;/a&#x3E;)&#x3C;/div&#x3E;</description>
