<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/DOMNOT">
<title>Domino, Brian: Nietzsche on the Struggle between Knowledge and Wisdom</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/DOMNOT</link>
<description>_Review of Metaphysics_ 47 (3):629-630. 1994May&#x27;s monograph concerns one aspect of the quarrel between the ancients and the moderns. He presents six meditations on the relation between wisdom and knowledge, taking his bearings from a free interpretation of Nietzsche&#x27;s Nachla&#xDF;. In an early notebook entry, Nietzsche remarks that science struggled with wisdom in the ancient Greek philosophers. That is, there was an agon between the salubrious but false Homeric myths and the &#x22;true&#x22; but toxic products of the drive toward knowledge. May attempts to resurrect this agon by reappraising knowledge and the soul.&#x3C;div&#x3E;(&#x3C;a href=&#x22;https://philpapers.org/go.pl?id=DOMNOT&#x26;amp;proxyId=&#x26;amp;u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pdcnet.org%2Fcollection%2Fshow%3Fid%3Drevmetaph_1994_0047_0003_0629_0630%26file_type%3Dpdf&#x22;&#x3E;direct link&#x3C;/a&#x3E;)&#x3C;/div&#x3E;</description>
