<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/RYAWKA">
<title>Ryan, Sharon: Wisdom, Knowledge and Rationality</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/RYAWKA</link>
<description>_Acta Analytica_ 27 (2):99-112. 2012After surveying the strengths and weaknesses of several well-known approaches to wisdom, I argue for a new theory of wisdom that focuses on being epistemically, practically, and morally rational. My theory of wisdom, The Deep Rationality Theory of Wisdom, claims that a wise person is a person who is rational and who is deeply committed to increasing his or her level of rationality. This theory is a departure from theories of wisdom that demand practical and/or theoretical knowledge. The Deep Rationality Theory salvages all that is attractive, and avoids all that is problematic, about theories of wisdom that require wise people to be knowledgeable.&#x3C;div&#x3E;(&#x3C;a href=&#x22;https://philpapers.org/go.pl?id=RYAWKA&#x26;amp;proxyId=&#x26;amp;u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mendeley.com%2Fresearch%2Fwisdom-knowledge-rationality%2F&#x22;&#x3E;direct link&#x3C;/a&#x3E;)&#x3C;/div&#x3E;</description>
