<item rdf:about="https://philpapers.org/rec/MAXTOT-2">
<title>Maxwell, Nicholas: Text of TEDxUCL Talk: The Urgent Need for an Academic Revolution</title>
<link>https://philpapers.org/rec/MAXTOT-2</link>
<description>We urgently need to bring about a revolution in academic inquiry so that the basic aim becomes, not just knowledge, but rather wisdom, construed to be the capacity and active endeavour to realize what is of value in life for oneself and others, wisdom thus including knowledge and technological know-how, but much else besides. A basic task of academia ought to be to help humanity learn how to make progress towards as good a world as possible.&#x3C;div&#x3E;(&#x3C;a href=&#x22;https://philpapers.org/go.pl?id=MAXTOT-2&#x26;amp;proxyId=&#x26;amp;u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Ddak-tDMSBUY&#x22;&#x3E;direct link&#x3C;/a&#x3E;)&#x3C;/div&#x3E;</description>
